To prove the inequality `‖f * g‖ₙ_[r] ≤ ‖f‖ₙ_[p] * ‖g‖ₙ_[q]` in the case where `p = ∞` (represented as `none` in `ℝ≥0∞` which is `WithTop ℝ≥0`), we first note that the Hölder condition `1/p + 1/q = 1/r` with `p = ∞` implies `1/q = 1/r`, and thus `q = r`.
The inequality then simplifies to `‖f * g‖ₙ_[q] ≤ ‖f‖ₙ_[∞] * ‖g‖ₙ_[q]`.
We use the fact that `‖f * g‖ₙ_[q]` is monotonic with respect to the pointwise bound `‖f i * g i‖ = ‖f i‖ * ‖g i‖ ≤ ‖f‖ₙ_[∞] * ‖g i‖`.
Using `cLpNorm_const_mul` (homogeneity), the right hand side is exactly `‖f‖ₙ_[∞] * ‖g‖ₙ_[q]`.

